# Diagnostics Scoping for Monorepos

**Status:** done · April 26 2026

## Problem
In a monorepo with multiple venvs / subprojects, the diagnostics panel and status-bar counts surfaced errors and warnings from the entire workspace. When working inside one subproject, sibling-subproject noise pushed real signal off-screen.

## Solution
Filter diagnostics to the **active subproject** — defined as the deepest venv whose `subdir` contains the currently-open file. Filtering is automatic when the workspace has ≥2 venvs and the active file lives under one of them; off otherwise.

## Implementation

### Stores (`src/lib/stores.ts`)
- `activeSubproject: string | null` — derived from `openFilePath` + `venvMap`. Returns the longest-prefix-matching `venvMap.subdir`.
- `diagnosticsScopeActive: boolean` — true when `venvMap.length ≥ 2` and `activeSubproject !== null`.
- `diagnosticsByUriFiltered` — derived view of `diagnosticsByUri`, narrowed to files under `activeSubproject` when scoping is active.
- `diagnostics` (counts) and `diagnosticFileSets` (path sets) now read from the filtered view.
- `diagnosticsTotal` — unfiltered counts, for the "N of M" affordance.

### UI surfaces auto-updated
- Status-bar diagnostic count (reads `diagnostics`).
- File-tree red/yellow dots (read `diagnosticFileSets`).
- Diagnostics modal item list (reads `diagnosticsByUriFiltered`).

### Affordance
DiagnosticsModal shows a small pill in the header when scoping is active:
`Scoped to <subproject_basename> · N of M` — click to expand to the full workspace view for the current modal session.

## Edge cases handled
- Active file outside any venv subdir → falls back to workspace-wide (no filter).
- Single-venv project → no filter (would degenerate to "everything").
- File ranks across multiple matching venvs → uses the deepest (longest path) match, mirroring how walk-up venv discovery works.

## Files touched
- `src/lib/stores.ts` — derived stores + helpers.
- `src/lib/DiagnosticsModal.svelte` — read filtered map, expand-to-workspace button, scope pill styling.

## Future work (not in scope here)
- Persisted user preference (`diagnostics.scope: 'subproject' | 'workspace'`) to override the auto-default.
- Group-by-subproject view in the diagnostics modal when scoping is off.
